Robinson: Both, and please your Worship ; I never meant wrong ;
but things have all gone wrong, and the sooner I get to rest, the better
pleased I shall be.

Robinson : Why then, Sir, master must get a coach as will go by
steam : it would be the making of 'Squire Lambton, your Worship ;
and as for hot water, the Opposition will keep 'um in that.
